Executive Profile
Dominic J. Pileggi  Independent Director, Acuity Brands, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships66$205,000
Background

		Mr. Dominic J. Pileggi served the Chief Executive Officer of Thomas & Betts Corp., from January 16, 2004 to May 2012. Mr. Pileggi began his career at Thomas & Betts in 1979 as a Sales Representative and progressed steadily through a variety of management positions until being named President of Lubrizol Corp.'s largest business, Electrical Products, in 1994. He served as President of Thomas & Betts Corp since January 2003. Mr. Pileggi held various positions with Thomas ... & Betts from 1979 to 1983 and served as Vice President and General Manager of the Electronics division from 1983 to 1986, Vice President of Electronics Marketing Division from 1986 to 1988, President of Electronics division from 1988 to 1994, President of Electrical Components Division from 1994 to 1995 and Senior Vice President from 2000 to 2002 of the Thomas & Betts. He began his career at Procter & Gamble. He served at Viasystems Group Inc., and as an Executive Vice President from 1998 to 2000 and President of EMS Division since 2000. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Casco Molded Plastics Inc., from 1995 to 1996. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and President of Jordan Telecommunications Products from 1996 to 1998. Mr. Pileggi served as Group President, Electrical of Thomas & Betts Corp., from 2000 to 2003 and served as Chief Operating Officer with responsibility for the strategic and operational leadership of Thomas & Betts's from 2003 to 2004. He has been the Chairman of Thomas & Betts Corp., since December 31, 2005 and its Director since 2004. He has been an Independent Director at Acuity Brands, Inc. since September 28, 2012. He served as a Director of Viasystems Group, Inc. from February 8, 2012 to May 31, 2015. He served as Director of Exide Technologies, Inc from 2010 to May 29, 2013. He served as an Independent Director of Lubrizol Corp., from February 21, 2005 to September 16, 2011 and its Lead Director from March 2007 to September 16, 2011. Mr. Pileggi holds an BA in Economics from Rutgers University.Read Full Background




